html(lang="fr" ng-app="facet")
  head
    meta(charset="utf-8")
    meta(http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=Edge")
    meta(
      name="viewport"
      content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no"
    )
    title Onitu - Sync and share your files
    link(rel="stylesheet" href="css/app.css")
  body
    #home
      .logo
        img(src="img/onitu.png", alt="Onitu")
      
      .text
        .container
          p
            | You are using lots of different web services ? You have files everywhere
            | and struggle to keep them synchronized ?
            | Install Onitu and take the control back over your data !
            
          .button
            a(href="https://github.com/onitu/onitu", target="_blank").
              Download on Github <i class="fa fa-github"></i>
      
    ul#icons
      li
        img(src="img/services/drive.png", alt="Google Drive")
      li
        img(src="img/services/dropbox-wide.png", alt="Dropbox")
      li
        img(src="img/services/evernote-wide.png", alt="Evernote")
      li
        img(src="img/services/flickr.png", alt="Flickr")
      li
        img(src="img/services/hubic.png", alt="Hubic")
      li
        img(src="img/services/s3.png", alt="Amazon S3")
      li
        img(src="img/services/ssh.png", alt="SSH")
          
    section#services
      .side
        .text
          h2 Your favorite services, together
          p
            | With Onitu you can use all your services (Dropbox, Drive, Evernote…) and share
            | any data between them. You want to save your notes from Evernote on your FTP server ?
            | No problem ! You want to edit your Dropbox files with Google Docs ? Easy peasy. You want
            | to put your laptop photos on Flickr ? Do it in a breeze.
      .side
        .media
          img(src="img/services.png")
    
    section#rules
      .side
        .media
          img(src="img/rules.png")

          
      .side
        .text
          h2 Your files, your rules
          p
            | Orchestrate your files with specific rules for them. You can say where
            | your files go according to their type, their size, their name, their path…
            | For example you can send your small Videos to Dropbox, the big ones to Hubic,
            | and backup all of them to your FTP server.
        
    section#install
      .side
        .text
          h2 Install it anywhere
          p
            | Onitu is a Free Software and you can install on any computer. It's a community-driven
            | project, there is no company behind it willing to steal your data or spy on you.
            | You can connect all your computers with our client.

      .side
        .media
          img(src="img/install.png")
          
    section#facet
      .side
        .media
          img(src="img/facet.png", alt="Facet web interface")
          
      .side
        .text
          h2 All your files in one place
          
          p
            | With the Web interface, you can see the files you have in your different
            | services, interact with them and control Onitu.
    
    section#team
      .container
        .col
          h2 <i class="fa fa-map-marker"></i> {Epitech}
          p
            | Onitu is an <a href="http://www.epitech.eu/epitech-innovative-projects.aspx" target="_blank">
            | Epitech Innovative Project</a>, which means that it has been
            | conceived by a team of students over the course of their 3rd, 4th
            | and 5th years. 10 students have worked hard on Onitu during these 3
            | years.
          
        .col
          h2 <i class="fa fa-github"></i> Open Source
          p
            | Onitu is a Free Software. Anybody can download it, change its
            | code and its behavior and redistribute it ! It's a project
            | driven by its community, not by any company or industry.<br>
            | Feel free to contribute !
          
        .col
          h2 <i class="fa fa-envelope"></i> Contact us
          p
            | If you have any question or issue regarding Onitu, the best place
            | to ask for help or support is the
            | <a href="https://github.com/onitu/onitu/issues" target="_blank">Issues page</a> on Github.
          
          ul
            li <i class="fa fa-slack"></i> IRC - #onitu on <a href="https://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=onitu" target="_blank">irc.freenode.org</a>
            li <i class="fa fa-twitter"></i> Twitter - <a href="http://twitter.com/onituproject" target="_blank">@OnituProject</a>
            li <i class="fa fa-envelope"></i> Mail - <a href="mailto:onitu_2015@labeip.epitech.eu">onitu_2015@labeip.epitech.eu</a>
